      Title:
        m_Untranslated: ChromaticAberrationPulse Script - Chaning the Intensity using
          Mathf.Sin()
      Text:
        m_Untranslated: 'In the <c>Update</c> function you can see that changing
          the intensity value itself is quite simple:

          <code>

          chromaticAberrationSetting.intensity.value
          = //something

          </code>

          The right-hand-side of this
          equation is a little trickier, but for the maths-nerds in the room should
          feel relatively comfortable. We just use a Sin-wave to set the value. A
          sin wave will modulate up and down over time, and we have some parameters
          we can use to adjust it:

          (image below from <a>https://www.shutterstock.com/image-vector/parts-wave-714187729</a>,
          thanks Google!)'
