    - m_Type: 0
      Title:
        m_Untranslated: ChromaticAberrationPulse Script - Chaning the Intensity using
          Mathf.Sin()
      Text:
        m_Untranslated: 'Using the diagram above, you should expect the following
          public variables which adjust the animation of the effect:

          <code>

          //the
          way to change this setting''s value over time

          public float sinMagnitude
          = 0.5f;

          public float sinOffset = 0.5f;

          public float
          speed = 10;

          </code>

          Which are then used in <c>Update</c>
          to set the value over time:

          <code>

          ...value = sinMagnitude
          * Mathf.Sin(Time.timeSinceLevelLoad * speed) + sinOffset;

          </code>

          Note
          we could have used an AnimationCurve here, but I wanted to illustrate another
          way we can change a value over time using pure code.'
